******
[2] Cholera - Mexico (Hidalgo State)
Date: Mon 21 Jul 2014
Source: AM [in Spanish, trans. Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ, edited]
http://www.am.com.mx/notareforma/57461


The Hidalgo Secretariat of Health (SSH) confirmed 4 new cases of cholera in the state, bringing the total to 9 people infected with the bacteria.

The assistant secretary for health of Hidalgo, Maria Dolores Osorio, said at a press conference that the new cases were reported in the municipality of Tetepango. She said the cases are 2 men and 2 women who, after laboratory studies, were confirmed as carriers of the disease.

Until last week [week of 14 Jul 2014], Hidalgo health officials had reported 2918 suspected cases of cholera in the state.

According to information from SSH, there have been 2 258 663 consultations, of which 2.58 per cent, that is 58 306, have required treatment and monitoring for acute diarrheal disease.

[byline: Fernando Paniagua]

