******
[3] Cholera - India: (Uttar Pradesh State)
Date: Wed 23 Jul 2014
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/City/Allahabad/Cholera-claims-two-lives/articleshow/38903970.cms


Cholera claimed 2 lives within last 48 hours in Khusda Khurd village [Uttar Pradesh State]. The health department officials claimed that the disease had broken out in the village on Monday [21 Jul 2014] and over a dozen persons with cholera symptoms were undergoing treatment at Manda community health center.

Chief medical officer [CMO] [in] Allahabad, Dr Padmakar Singh told TOI, "1 person died of the disease on Monday evening while another died here on Tuesday morning [22 Jul 2014]." The 2 persons had developed acute gastroenteritis (one of the symptoms of cholera) that had led to their death. He added that 2 medical teams have been pressed into service to take care of patients undergoing treatment at the community health center.

The CMO further maintained that initial report indicated [that a] supply of contaminated water [was] behind the spread of disease besides unhygienic conditions also prevailing in the village. Apart from health officials, 2 special constituted medical teams were campaigning in the area and carrying out examination of villagers. The officials, however, maintained that the situation in the village was under control as people are being advised to take precautions while consuming water. They were also told about the measures that are helpful in checking the status of potable water.

Health authorities have also distributed medicines in the village and set up a makeshift dispensary. Meanwhile, the district administration is ascertaining the source of water that was consumed by the villagers after which they fell ill.

